@startuml
title Patron ModelForm / Form Object - Validacion antes de persistir

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam defaultFontName Arial

class OrderForm <<ModelForm>> {
  +clean_order_number()
  +save()
}

class OrderItemForm <<ModelForm>> {
  +clean_quantity()
  +clean_unit_price()
  +clean()
  +save()
}

class RecordForm <<ModelForm>>
class SignUpForm <<UserCreationForm>>

class Order {
  +order_number
  +status
  +payment_status
}

class OrderItem {
  +product_name
  +quantity
  +unit_price
}

class Record {
  +first_name
  +last_name
  +email
}

class "Django User" as User

OrderForm ..> Order : valida y guarda
OrderItemForm ..> OrderItem : valida y guarda
RecordForm ..> Record : valida y guarda
SignUpForm ..> User : crea usuario

class OrderItemFormSet <<Factory Method result>> {
  +is_valid()
  +save()
}

OrderItemFormSet ..> OrderItemForm : agrupa formularios
OrderItemFormSet ..> Order : padre
OrderItemFormSet ..> OrderItem : hijos

note right of OrderForm
Convencion Django, no GoF:
el formulario encapsula entrada,
widgets, errores y validaciones.
end note

note bottom of OrderItemFormSet
inlineformset_factory crea esta clase
configurada para la relacion Order-OrderItem.
end note

@enduml
